erything from the simple \"taste of your childhood\", to elaborate constructions featuring bespoke breads and gourmet cheeses. The Cheesus, a burger with the buns replaced by grilled cheese sandwiches, is justifiably notorious. It runs three carts now – one in a London double-decker bus – it seems everyone loves a bit of gourmet grilled cheese.<br />• <a href=\"http://grilledcheesegrill.com/\" title=\"\"><em>grilledcheesegrill.com</em></a></p><h2>Artigiano</h2><figure data-media-id='gu-image-438166388'><img src='http://static.guim.co.uk/sys-images/Travel/Pix/pictures/2014/5/29/1401364674772/Portland-top-10-Artigiano-001.jpg' alt='Portland top 10 Artigiano' width='460' height='276' class='gu-image'/><figcaption> </figcaption></figure><p>Cordon Bleu-trained chef Rachael Grossman prides herself on the fine-dining quality of food that issues from her mobile kitchen: yukon gold gnocchi with caramelised onions and cream; pasta handmade daily in the cart's tiny kitchen. You can leave it to her, with a tasting feast served family-style. It's even licensed.<br />• <a href=\"http://www.artigianopdx.com/\" title=\"\"><em>artigianopdx.com</em></a></p><h2>Tiffin Asha</h2><figure data-media-id='gu-image-438166389'><img src='http://static.guim.co.uk/sys-images/Guardian/Pix/pictures/2014/5/30/1401444584667/Tiffin-Asha-Portland-001.jpg' alt='Tiffin Asha, Portland' width='460' height='358' class='gu-image'/><figcaption></figcaption></figure><p>Foodie author Karen Brooks says: \"Only Portland can offer you pakora-fried chicken wrapped in a dosa and served from a colourful food cart window. Think exotic chicken McNuggets, gloriously dunked and fried in spicy chickpea-rice flour, then wrapped in a dosa glazed with <em>neyyi</em> (clarified butter) and local yoghurt. The crispy-tangy dosa cone pops with spice, crunch and surprise. This is fried chicken and greens reborn, ecstatically. I could eat it every day.\"<br />• <a href=\"http://tiffinasha.com/\" title=\"\"><em>tiffinasha.com</em></a></p><h2>Weenies From Another World</h2><figure data-media-id='gu-image-438166390'><img src='http://static.guim.co.uk/sys-images/Travel/Pix/pictures/2014/5/29/1401364612040/Portland-top-10-weenies-f-001.jpg' alt='Portland top 10 weenies from another world' width='460' height='405' class='gu-image'/><figcaption> </figcaption></figure><p>I'm almost tempted to say who cares what the food is like, when the cart is so gorgeous. This one is like a cross between a vintage Airstream caravan and a UFO as designed by the Jetsons. But close attention to detail is paid with the food, too: locally made dogs and bread from the <a href=\"http://www.helenbernhardbakery.com/\" title=\"\">Helen Bernhard bakery</a>, fluffy little tater tots. Make mine a Louisiana Hot \"Flash Gordon\" with deep-fried zucchini.<br />• <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/pages/Weenies-From-Another-World/101539866599994\" title=\"\"><em>Facebook page</em></a></p><h2>Gonzo Falafel and Hummus</h2><figure data-media-id='gu-image-438166391'><img src='http://static.guim.co.uk/sys-images/Travel/Pix/pictures/2014/5/29/1401365795210/Portland-top-10-Gonzo-fel-001.jpg' alt='Portland top 10 Gonzo felafel and hummus' width='460' height='330' class='gu-image'/><figcaption> </figcaption></figure><p>According to Karen Brooks: \"Gonzo's owner, Tal Caspi, considers every element: from scratch-cooked garbanzos to crisp fries teetering on top, though I'm more a sucker for his Shawarma fries, a&nbsp;beautiful mess of curry-clad chicken, thick-cut fries, hummus, tahini and a condiment hotter than brimstone fire.\" Basically Israeli <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Poutine\" title=\"\">poutine</a>, then. Bring it on.<br />• <a href=\"http://www.iheartfalafel.com/\" title=\"\"><em>iheartfalafel.com</em></a><em>  </em></p><h2>Carte Blanche</h2><figure data-media-id='gu-image-438166392'><img src='http://static.guim.co.uk/sys-images/Travel/Pix/pictures/2014/5/29/1401364147934/Portland-top-10-Carte-Bla-001.jpg' alt='Portland top 10 Carte Blanche' width='460' height='330' class='gu-image'/><figcaption> </figcaption></figure><p>Pretty much defying categories, this ultra-cute trailer's owner, Jessie, says the style of cooking is \"completely our own\", mixing it up with a dizzying range of eclectic components: kaffir lime leaves in coconut milk to rosemary beets and beer-braised ribs. The result isn't the mishmash you'd expect (despite the eccentric dish names).<br />• <em><a href=\"http://www.carteblanchefoodcart.com/\">carteblanchefoodcart.com</a></em></p><h2>Miss Kate's Southern Kitchen</h2><figure data-media-id='gu-image-438166393'><img src='http://static.guim.co.uk/sys-images/Guardian/Pix/pictures/2014/5/30/1401444355265/Miss-Kates-Southern-Kitch-001.jpg' alt='Miss Kate's Southern Kitchen' width='460' height='327' class='gu-image'/><figcaption></figcaption></figure><p>This folksy cart dishes out Southern comfort food: freshly made mac 'n' cheese, pumpkin-spiced waffles with maple butter, meatloaf and <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Succotash\" title=\"\">succotash</a>. Also come for the chicken, marinated in brown sugar and hot sauce, fried till crisp outside and juicy within, glazed with maple syrup and served with buttery, fluffy biscuits (like savoury scones) and bacon gravy. It is a Very Bad Thing in the best possible way.<br />• <a href=\"http://www.misskatessouthernkitchen.com/\" title=\"\"><em>misskatessouthernkitchen.com</em></a></p><h2>Koi Fusion</h2><figure data-media-id='gu-image-438166394'><img src='http://static.guim.co.uk/sys-images/Travel/Pix/pictures/2014/5/29/1401365405867/Portland-top-10-Koi-Fusio-001.jpg' alt='Portland top 10, Koi Fusion' width='460' height='380' class='gu-image'/><figcaption> </figcaption></figure><p>Bo Kwon's blockbuster fuses Korean and Mexican flavours with local and organic ingredients: barbecue <em>bulgogi</em> or <em>kalbi</em> in tacos and burritos, <em>kimchi</em> in <em>quesadillas</em>. It's a surprisingly successful double act. The Seoul sliders are as moreish as meaty Maltesers.<br />• <a href=\"http://koifusionpdx.com/\" title=\"\"><em>koifusionpdx.com</em></a><em> </em></p><h2>Picnic</h2><figure data-media-id='gu-image-438166395'><img src='http://static.guim.co.uk/sys-images/Travel/Pix/pictures/2014/5/29/1401364390360/Portland-top-10-Picnic-001.jpg' alt='Portland top 10 Picnic' width='460' height='322' class='gu-image'/><figcaption> </figcaption></figure><p>Picnic looks like a hobbit's beach hut, as cute and bucolic as its setting is urban and grungey. Owner John Dovydenas' sandwiches (a small word for a big feast) have become cult must-haves in a city overloaded with choice, perhaps because, even for the simple BLT, his bread is homemade and his bacon comes from a Portland pig brined with honey and black pepper, then cherrywood-smoked for six hours. He calls it \"Oregon trail cuisine\". The \"cart-cured\" corn beef reuben is a thing of beauty.<br />• <a href=\"http://pdxpicnic.com/\" title=\"\"><em>pdxpicnic.com</em></a><em> </em></p>","headline":"Top 10 food trucks in Portland, Oregon","trailText":"<p>There are hundreds of gourmet food trucks in Portland, serving up some of the most exhilarating street food <strong>Marina O'Loughlin</strong> has ever eaten. Here she picks 10 carts to try</p>","newspaperPageNumber":"8","shouldHideAdverts":"false","publication":"The Guardian","showInRelatedContent":"true","thumbnail":"http://static.guim.co.uk/sys-images/Travel/Pix/pictures/2014/5/29/1401365065180/Portland-top-10-Nongs-Kha-006.jpg","wordcount":"656","commentable":"true","internalContentCode":"437905136","allowUgc":"false","internalOctopusCode":"9089218","isPremoderated":"false","byline":"Marina O'Loughlin","newspaperEditionDate":"2014-05-31T00:00:00Z","internalPageCode":"2099551","productionOffice":"UK","liveBloggingNow":"false","commentCloseDate":"2014-06-02T13:23:00Z"},"webUrl":"http://www.theguardian.com/travel/2014/may/30/top-10-food-trucks-portland-oregon","apiUrl":"http://beta.cont